<paragraph id="8BB3C83D7729707AFF2AFAB6FB6EFEC0" blockId="4.[136,1452,158,293]" pageId="4" pageNumber="75">
<emphasis id="B978142F7729707AFF2AFAB6FE1AFF5C" box="[189,416,159,185]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="75">Conservation status</emphasis>
:— 
<taxonomicName id="4C0CB3BE7729707AFE53FAB6FD9AFF5C" authorityName="Salgado, Wenzel" authorityYear="2021" box="[452,544,158,185]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Aspleniaceae" genus="Asplenium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="75" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pahli">
<emphasis id="B978142F7729707AFE53FAB6FD9AFF5C" box="[452,544,158,185]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="75">A. pahli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was collected in an area near the towns of Dagami and Jaro that is presently denuded of its original primary growth forest (
<bibRefCitation id="EF9DB5CC7729707AFD05FAEBFCE2FF38" author="Lasco, R. D. &amp; Visco, R. G. &amp; Pulhin, J. M." box="[658,856,194,220]" pageId="4" pageNumber="75" pagination="652 - 670" refId="ref5497" refString="Lasco, R. D., Visco, R. G. &amp; Pulhin, J. M. (2001) Secondary forests in the Philippines: Formation and transformation in the 20 th century. Journal of Tropical Forest Science 13: 652 - 670. Available from: https: // www. researchgate. net / publication / 239592580 _ Secondary _ forests _ in _ the _ Philippines _ Formation _ and _ transformation _ in _ the _ 20 th _ century (accessed 3 November 2020)" type="journal article" year="2001">
Lasco 
<emphasis id="B978142F7729707AFD49FAEAFCACFF38" box="[734,790,194,220]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="75">et al.</emphasis>
2001
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9DB5CC7729707AFCF3FAEBFB9AFF38" author="Mongabay" box="[868,1056,194,220]" pageId="4" pageNumber="75" refId="ref5831" refString="Mongabay (2020) Deforestation statistics for the Philippines. Available from: https: // rainforests. mongabay. com / deforestation / archive / Philippines. htm (accessed 8 September 2020)" type="url" year="2020">Mongabay 2020</bibRefCitation>
). The only collection known is that of Wenzel in 1914. This is a possible indication that 
<taxonomicName id="4C0CB3BE7729707AFD5EFACEFC9BFEE4" authorityName="Salgado, Wenzel" authorityYear="2021" box="[713,801,230,257]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Aspleniaceae" genus="Asplenium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="75" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pahli">
<emphasis id="B978142F7729707AFD5EFACEFC9BFEE4" box="[713,801,230,257]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="75">A. pahli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endangered or possibly extinct in its 
<typeStatus id="54B7769F7729707AFB42FACEFABFFEE5" box="[1237,1285,231,257]" pageId="4" pageNumber="75">type</typeStatus>
locality. There might be more plants scattered in the remaining stands of old growth deep in the 
<collectingRegion id="49C806DF7729707AFB83FB22FBEEFEC1" box="[1044,1108,267,293]" country="Philippines" name="Southern Leyte" pageId="4" pageNumber="75">Leyte</collectingRegion>
Cordillera.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB3C83D7729707AFF1FFB62FECFFE6D" blockId="4.[136,1451,331,393]" pageId="4" pageNumber="75">
<emphasis id="B978142F7729707AFF1FFB62FD05FE81" box="[136,703,331,358]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="75">
<taxonomicName id="4C0CB3BE7729707AFF1FFB62FECCFE81" authorityName="G. Forster" authorityYear="1786" box="[136,374,331,357]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Aspleniaceae" genus="Asplenium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="75" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="caudatum">Asplenium caudatum</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0CB3BE7729707AFE16FB65FDBFFE81" authorityName="Lamarck" authorityYear="1786" box="[385,517,331,358]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Aspleniaceae" genus="Asplenium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="75" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="falcatum">A. falcatum</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0CB3BE7729707AFD98FB65FD05FE81" authorityName="C. Presl, Cuming" authorityYear="1849" box="[527,703,331,358]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Aspleniaceae" genus="Asplenium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="75" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="anisodontum">A. anisodontum</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C0CB3BE7729707AFD62FB65FCF4FE81" authorityName="Salgado, Wenzel" authorityYear="2021" box="[757,846,331,358]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Aspleniaceae" genus="Asplenium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="75" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pahli">
<emphasis id="B978142F7729707AFD62FB65FCF4FE81" box="[757,846,331,358]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="75">A. pahli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
represent different species as shown by the characters presented in this key.
</paragraph>
